We can compute LPS[i] using the following logic:

* If S[i-1] matches the last character of the longest proper prefix of S[0..i-2], then LPS[i] = LPS[i-1] + 1
* Otherwise, we try to find the largest index j < i-1 such that S[j] = S[i-1] and LPS[j] = i - j - 1. If such an index exists, then LPS[i] = j + 1.

Now we can compute dp[i] using the following recurrence relation:

* dp[i] = sum(dp[j]) for all j such that 0 <= j < i and LPS[j] = i - j - 1

This recurrence relation handles the case where the substring that we delete from M has its last character in the position j and its first character in the position i - j - 1. The value of dp[0] is taken to be 1.

