To turn the pairing into a sequence, we can use a depth-first search (DFS) starting with an arbitrary node in the matching. During the DFS, whenever we visit a node for the first time, we add it to the current sequence, and whenever we backtrack to a node, we swap its position with the node that follows it in the sequence. This ensures that each pair of nodes in the matching is adjacent in the sequence after the swap.

